f two bearers of the same name in a family. This surname was brought to the US mainly from Haiti, where it is most common."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Elye","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: variant of   Ells   or   Ellis  .","North German: topographic name for someone who lived by an alder or alders, Middle Low German <i>else</i>, or a habitational name from any of various places formed with this word."],"variants":[{"name":"Els","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Ewald, Wilhelm.","German: variant of   Else  ."]},{"name":"Ells","meanings":["English (London and Kent): variant of   Ellis  , or a variant of   Ell  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":40,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":49,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"William Fils Elye was born in 1175, in Corston, Wiltshire, England. He had at least 2 sons with Emma de Braie. He died in 1226, in Corston, Somerset, England, at the age of 51."},"et":{"1175–1226":"1175–1226","1179–Female":"1179–Surnud","–1230":"–1230","1200–1240":"1200–1240","1225–1262":"1225–1262","–Female":"Surnud","1226":"1226","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","1200":"1200","1175":"1175","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1240":"1240","Corston, Wiltshire, Eng.":"Corston, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Corston, Somerset, England":"Corston, Somerset, England","England":"England","Corston, Wiltshire, England":"Corston, Wiltshire, England"},"fi":{"1175–1226":"1175–1226","1179–Female":"1179–Kuollut","–1230":"–1230","1200–1240":"1200–1240","1225–1262":"1225–1262","–Female":"Kuollut","1226":"1226","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","1200":"1200","1175":"1175","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1240":"1240","Corston, Wiltshire, Eng.":"Corston, Wiltshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Corston, Somerset, England":"Corston, Somerset, England","England":"England","Corston, Wiltshire, England":"Corston, Wiltshire, England"},"fr":{"1175–1226":"1175–1226","1179–Female":"1179–Décédée","–1230":"–1230","1200–1240":"1200–1240","1225–1262":"1225–1262","–Female":"Décédée","1226":"1226","1215":"1215","1225":"1225","1224":"1224","1179":"1179","1200":"1200","1175":"1175","1230":"1230","1262":"1262","1240":"1240","Corston, Wiltshire, Eng.":"Corston, Wiltshire, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Corston, Somerset, England":"Corston, Somerset, Angleterre","England":"Anglet